<p>Choosing the right words can be challenging, but sincerity is key. Avoid generic phrases and instead, focus on your personal relationship with the deceased and your connection with the bereaved. Remember to be respectful of their grief, acknowledging their loss without minimizing their pain. Let your message reflect your genuine feelings of sympathy and your willingness to offer support during their time of mourning.  Consider the relationship you had with both the deceased and the recipient when selecting your words.</p>
    

